 <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">Nonlocal energy density functionals for pairing and beyond-mean-field calculations</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">IOP</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">We propose to use two-body regularized finite-range pseudopotential to generate nuclear energy density functional (EDF) in both particle–hole and particle–particle channels, which makes it free from self-interaction and self-pairing, and also free from singularities when used beyond mean field. We derive a sequence of pseudopotentials regularized up to next-to-leading order and next-to-next-to-leading order, which fairly well describe infinite-nuclear-matter properties and finite open-shell paired and/or deformed nuclei. Since pure two-body pseudopotentials cannot generate sufficiently large effective mass, the obtained solutions constitute a preliminary step towards future implementations, which will include, e.g., EDF terms generated by three-body pseudopotentials.</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">IOP</subfield>
 </datafield>
